item.description:
arXiv:2507.19506v1 Announce Type: new 
Abstract: In this paper, we mainly prove that if $H$ is a closed strong subgyrogroup of a strongly topological gyrogroup $G$ and $H$ is neutral, then
  (1) $G/H$ is biradial if and only if $G/H$ is nested;
  (2) $G/H$ is metrizable if and only if $G/H$ is a biradial space with countable pseudocharacter;
  (3) $G/H$ is metrizable if and only if $G/H$ has countable $cn$-character, given that $G/H$ has the Baire property.
